{
    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix incorrect SSB-to-preamble mapping in 2-step RA procedures\n\n### Summary\nThe NR UE MAC layer had an issue with 2-step random access procedure where the code was always selecting the first SSB resource (index 0) for preamble selection, regardless of which SSB was actually detected and selected by the UE. This caused RA failures when the network expected a preamble corresponding to a different SSB than the first one.\n\nThe bug was in the `nr_get_prach_resources` function which hardcoded the SSB resource index to 0 instead of using the `ssb_nb_in_ro` field that indicates the actual selected SSB.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/LAYER2/NR_MAC_UE/nr_ra_procedures.c`: \n  * Added new static function `get_ssb_ro_preambles_2step` to properly map selected SSB to its corresponding preamble\n  * Updated `nr_get_prach_resources` to use the selected SSB index instead of hardcoded index 0\n  * Added support for both standard CFRA and Rel-16 2-step CFRA configurations\n  * Included proper error handling and fallback logic\n\n"
}